# Rose Empire — stability rules

## Live payments
- `site-config.js` must keep `checkoutApiUrl` on `https://rose-empire-checkout.adeelcolchester.workers.dev` for both local preview and production.
- Never point the public site at local Flask Stripe unless the user explicitly wants test-only local keys.
- Never commit Stripe secret keys, `.env`, or Cloudflare `.dev.vars`.

## Cart + Sarah
- While the quote cart is open, Sarah must stay hidden (`body.cart-drawer-open` + hide `#sarah-widget` / launcher / nudge / panel). Removing this breaks live checkout clicks (Sarah uses max z-index).
- Keep the black/gold Sarah orb from the Cloudflare widget; do not confuse browser extensions (e.g. QuillBot yellow dots) with site UI.

## Deploy
- GitHub Pages must deploy only the allowlisted public `site/` files — never the whole repo (no `server.py`, secrets, or tooling).
- After frontend changes that affect checkout/cart, bump the `?v=` cache query on CSS/JS in `index.html` (and sector pages if they load the same assets).
- Run `python scripts/check_secrets.py`, `python scripts/check_site_config.py`, and optionally `python scripts/smoke_live.py` before calling the site “done”.

## Scope
- Keep this repo as the wholesale website + Sarah + Stripe path. Do not reintroduce scrapers, fleet bots, LinkedIn tooling, or unrelated automation.
